The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), will on Saturday address Nigerians in commemoration of this year’s Democracy Day. The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, disclosed this in a statement titled ‘President Buhari broadcasts to the nation, June 12, 2021.’ The statement read, “To commemorate Nigeria’s Democracy Day, June 12, 2021, President Muhammadu Buhari will address the nation on Saturday, June 12, 2021, at 7am. “Television, radio stations and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority and Radio Nigeria for the broadcast.”